The paper discusses the emergence and properties of rich clubs in networks, which are relevant to various fields in computer science such as social networks, network analysis, and data mining. The paper also presents a modification algorithm for inserting rich centrality clubs within networks, which falls under the category of network algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.SD (software engineering), cs.NI (networking and internet architecture), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.LG (machine learning).
